   <h1>Re: [VB] Bus Depot is Hiring!</h1>
   <b>Ken Alford &lt;labmission_at_earthlink_dot_net&gt;</b><br/>
   <i>2001-08-27 08:18:36+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>"The Bus Depot, Inc." wrote:
> 
> Once again, as our summer college help goes back to school, we are in dire
> need of more employees.
> Please email me, or call Dan at 215-234-VWVW if interested.
> 
> - Ron Salmon
>   The Bus Depot, Inc.
>   (215) 234-VWVW
>   www.busdepot_dot_com
>

Hi Ron and all you old timers on the VB list.
Last time I pmailed Ron on the last hire go round...
Something about being over qualified??? Things have changed...
It looks as if things go as planed, I will have a Employment gap until 
January. I'd love to spend it in a bus related job.
Are you up for a long explanation of my current situation? Here goes:
I'm broke in Hawaii.
yeah yeah in know; boo hoo! Poor beach bum... I'm, ah, between careers.
I learned Navapache Regional Medical Center in Show Low, AZ
is looking for new tech.s. They approached me with the idea to get 
my National Certificate through a Med. tech Certification program
starting in the Spring of '02. (hence the wait / gap in work)
They would sponsor my schooling, in return, I would agree to work 
for them; 30K salery... woohoo! Think of all the VW parts I could buy. 
They scheduled me for 3 days with hotel and car thrown in.
I fly out of  Honolulu on the 10th of September. My interview is/ 
are on the 11th and 12th and I fly out of Phoenix on the 13th... 
I could on the mainland and catch the bus to CA (or PA) 
and look for work rather than returning to Honolulu.
My Kombi is in storage in Coalinga, California, (near Fresno) 
You may remember from the list on new year's 1998-99 My dove blue 61
Kombi threw a rod as I was on the last hill going north into Tucson. 
I was coming back to the west Coast after finishing school in Florida.
I was able to obtain a new motor at Chirco Automotive and install 
it in the bus using a church's parking lot. 
(On New Years Eve, what fun!) 
So you see, I've got some travel experience in a Bus... 
loaf and split; all with upright motors. 
Here's a resume:


Ken Alford
84-1035 Kaula'ili Rd.
Waianae HI 96792
labmission_at_earthlink_dot_com
http://home.earthlink_dot_net/~labmission/index.html
(808) 695 0196
 
Education	
Auto Body and Fender Repair R.O.P. Corning, CA
Auto Shop, Metal shop, AG shop, Welding, etc. J.C. and H.S.
Cert. computer literate; word processors, spread sheets, data entry.
A.S. Electronic Technology Butte College Oroville, CA
Bachelor of Science in Biology at Clearwater Christian College CW, FL

Experience	
My most recent experience is in handy man for my landlady and for 
various people on the leeward side of Oahu;  Mechanic, yard work, 
electrical, etc. Last year I worked as a mechanic for a wholesale 
/retail industrial small engine warehouse / shop. My duties included; 
customer service , estimates , repair scheduling, parts look up, 
data entry on computer, mechanic, cashiering, cleanup. I had some 
other jobs with the same duties plus sales (in college etc.) 
§	Small Engine Clinic, Aiea, HI
§	The Bike Shop, Aiea, HI
§	Rising Sun Engines, Chico, CA

In the engineering work force and other jobs locally 	
My most recent clinical experience was in hospital STAT lab.
I was involved in component production and robotics and as consumer 
electronic bench technician, along with touring nationally & overseas 
as engineer for performing arts productions.  
More recently I did Electrician Helper work, residential & commercial.
§	Diagnostic Laboratory Services/ Accupath, Honolulu, HI (4yrs)
§	Continental Singers and Orchestra, Thousand Oaks, CA
§	Sims Electric, Palm Harbor, FL  
§	Service Robotics, Chico, CA</pre>


